My family and I decided to support this business for Mother's day and had a terrible experience that ruined our holiday plans. We waited over 3 hours to receive our food while requests to speak to the owner or manager fell on deaf ears. Staff could not provide us with an estimate as to how long we would have to wait. They simply instructed us to "check back every 15 minutes". Social distancing rules were not being adhered to at all as customer crowded the establishment demanding updates on their orders. When our order did finally come, it was missing 5 dishes that we had already been charged for. We had to wait an additional 20 minutes for the order to be rectified. The food was not well seasoned and the lobster was very overcooked and had to be discarded as it simply was inedible. Additionally, there seemed to be boxes of raw seafood left to thaw on the main floor in plain view of the patrons. When questioned, the staff stated they had no idea why the food was left there. That is an issue that could have potentially sickened hundreds of customers. Never again will we dine at this establishment.
